{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow Landlords to Ask for a Higher Deposit from Tenants With Pets",
        "additional_details": "Through out my search for rental accommodation, I\u2019ve encountered several landlords that asked from an extra \u00a320 to \u00a325 per month per pet. This is to cover any damages the pet might cause to the property. Sadly, over time this accumulates to more money than needed to cover any damages the pet might do, and it is unfair on pet owners with pets that don\u2019t cause much damage to the property.",
        "background": "Currently, the law only allows 5 weeks deposit to be paid in advance on rental properties, however this is causing landlords to charge a higher rent from pet owners. I am proposing that landlords should be able to charge a \u2018pet deposit\u2019 on top of the security deposit.",
